# Why the Sun Has Not Burnt Out

## Core Claim
The Sun is **not** powered primarily by internal nuclear fusion. It is a **plasma vortex** sustained by external energy from the **Galactic current sheet** and ingested interstellar material. This resolves the Sun's anomalous longevity, the coronal heating mystery, and early-universe star formation seen by JWST.

## Flaws in the Standard Model
- Finite hydrogen fuel predicts ~10 billion year lifespan; our Sun (~4.6 Gyr old) shows no depletion signs.
- Core fusion cannot explain the million-degree corona vs. cooler surface.
- Early mature galaxies (z > 14) contradict rapid stellar burnout in a young universe.

## SRC Explanation: Plasma Vortex on Galactic Currents
